   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note type="caution" id="note_kjy_cm5_jcc" class="- topic/note ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">In an emergency, or if there is a risk of injury or damage to property or the
                  environment, either: </p>
            </note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "/>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Stop the lifting station at the control panel by pressing the Start/Stop button.  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Press the E-Stop for the lifting station. This will also stop all SBS operations,
                     including the pneumatic sender.   </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" id="note_zqs_fm5_jcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">When the E-Stop button is pressed, all movements of the lifting station are
                     stopped, and pneumatic cylinders end their stroke after reaching the end
                     position. </p>
               </note>
               <note type="note" id="note_bbh_gm5_jcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Frequent emergency stops result in high mechanical loads and increased wear.
                  </p>
               </note>
            </info>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig id="fig_lyh_2m5_jcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                         placement="break"
                         id="image_myh_2m5_jcc"
                         align="center"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note type="note" id="note_fps_gm5_jcc" class="- topic/note ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The gate in the safety fence is equipped with a safety limit switch. When the gate
                  is opened, an E-Stop occurs that stops the lifting station and the rest of SBS.
               </p>
            </note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Follow these steps to enter the fenced area: </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Inform the operating personnel and the batch supervisor that maintenance is
                     being performed.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Stop the lifting station at the MSK control panel by pressing the Start/Stop
                     button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">In the MSK control cabinet in the control room, trip the 3 circuit breakers. <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Remove the circuit breakers.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Lockout-tagout-verify the power per plant requirements.</li>
                     </ul>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">At the safety fence door, press the Request Door Open button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">When the light turns green, open the gate. Then close it after entering.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Press th<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">e Door Reset</uicontrol> (blue) button.  </li>
               </ul>
            </info>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig id="fig_v4b_3m5_jcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                         placement="break"
                         id="image_w4b_3m5_jcc"
                         align="center"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
               <fig id="fig_vd3_3m5_jcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                         placement="break"
                         id="image_wd3_3m5_jcc"
                         align="center"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">After completing the maintenance work:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Make sure that the equipment can operate properly.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Verify that all safety components are in place.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">When leaving the fenced area, press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Door Reset</uicontrol>
                     button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Remove LOTO, and re-install the 3 circuit breakers in the MSK control cabinet.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">At the control panel, cancel all faults by pressing the Reset Fault button on the control panel.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Also, press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Reset Safety Fence Area </uicontrol>button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Ensure that no personnel are near the equipment, or in the safety fence area.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Press the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Start</uicontrol> button on the control panel.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Observe the operation to ensure that the lifting station is working properly.  </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="caution" id="note_acf_rm5_jcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p "> There is a serious danger for anyone inside the safety fence area when the
                     lifting station is turned on. </p>
               </note>
            </info>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig id="fig_d5c_km5_jcc" class="- topic/fig ">
